  {
    "content_id": 159046,
    "reference_id": 25105,
    "title": "提多書 1:15–16",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56001015-56001016",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>這兩節經文評述<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:14\">一章14節</a>所提到的人及其命令，同時也過渡到對鼓勵行善教導的討論（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus3:11\">2:1–3:11</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56001015",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 1:15",
          "end_ref": "56001016",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 1:16"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159048,
    "reference_id": 25107,
    "title": "提多書 1:16",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56001016",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>純全的教導和敬虔在提摩太前後書及提多書中總是緊密相連（見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:7-1Tim1:11\">提前1:7–11</a>，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:15-1Tim3:16\">3:15–16</a>，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:24-1Tim5:25\">5:24–25</a>；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:5\">提後3:5</a>、<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:9\">9</a>）。同樣，他們不敬虔的生活方式也總是與錯誤的教導有關。</p></li><li><p>各樣善事：這與<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">提多書三章1節</a>形成對比。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56001016",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 1:16",
          "end_ref": "56001016",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 1:16"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159059,
    "reference_id": 25118,
    "title": "提多書 2:1–15",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002001-56002015",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>由於假教師在「人的全家」中帶來問題，因此健全的教導尤為迫切（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:11\">1:11</a>）。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus2:10\">二章1至10節</a>中，保羅提及信仰家庭中的不同群體，表達了他對教會公開見證的關注（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:5\">2:5</a>、<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:8\">8</a>、<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:10\">10</a>；另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1-1Tim6:2\">提前5:1–6:2</a>）。隨後，保羅詳細說明了基督的來臨（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11-Titus2:14\">多2:11–14</a>），並給了提多直接的指示（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:15\">2:15</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:1",
          "end_ref": "56002015",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:15"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159065,
    "reference_id": 25124,
    "title": "提多書 2:9–10",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002009-56002010",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>這些勸告的目的是「尊榮神的道」。<span>庇哩亞聖經（Berean Standard Bible）</span>這樣翻譯：「神的教導變得吸引人（...adorn the teaching about God...）」（見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1-1Tim6:2\">提前6:1–2</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002009",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:9",
          "end_ref": "56002010",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:10"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159061,
    "reference_id": 25120,
    "title": "提多書 2:11",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002011",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>已經顯明出來（字面意思是<em>已經出現</em>）：見<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"16535\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleStudyNotes\">提前6:14的研讀註釋</span>。</p></li><li><p>救眾人的恩典：保羅希望神的恩典能夠在克里特人中完全實現其旨意，並且透過如此，使他們參與到神的福音傳播救贖工作中（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">多2:12</a>；見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:7\">提前2:1–7</a>，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:10\">4:10</a>）。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002011",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:11",
          "end_ref": "56002011",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:11"
        }
      ],
      "resource": [
        {
          "reference_id": 16535,
          "content_id": 313639,
          "resource_code": "TyndaleStudyNotes",
          "label": "提摩太前書 6:14",
          "language": "zht"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159060,
    "reference_id": 25119,
    "title": "提多書 2:11–15",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002011-56002015",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>因為：<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus2:10\">二章1至10節</a>的命令是建立在基督過去的降臨和未來來臨的基礎上。神的恩典是教會行為的榜樣，就如同憑恩典而得救，使得美善生命成為可能，並且使人致力於行善（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3-Titus3:7\">3:3–7</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002011",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:11",
          "end_ref": "56002015",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:15"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159062,
    "reference_id": 25121,
    "title": "提多書 2:12",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002012",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>教訓（instructs）我們：這些教導的重點在於積極的美德：智慧、公義和對神的虔誠（devotion）。在希臘羅馬的著作中，這三種美德一般代表德行。這些美德對應在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:12\">一章12節</a>中列出的克里特人的惡行（不道德的行為或特質），並徹底地轉化為基督徒的品格（見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13\">2:13</a>）。</p></li><li><p>保羅勸勉克里特人擁有這些美德，從而清楚地向他們的同胞展示：有德行的生命只源於神在耶穌基督裡的恩典。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002012",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:12",
          "end_ref": "56002012",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:12"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 159063,
    "reference_id": 25122,
    "title": "提多書 2:13",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "56002013",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>等候：這意味著盼望以及未來的責任，這兩者都鼓勵現在就過敬虔的生活。</p></li><li><p>顯現：這裡使用的希臘字，在提摩太前後書和提多書中特別重要（「顯現」或「出現」；另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11\">2:11</a>；見<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"16535\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleStudyNotes\">提前6:14的研讀註釋</span>）。</p></li><li><p>至大的神和救主：這是新約聖經中少數幾個明確稱耶穌基督為「神」的地方之一（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1\">約翰福音1:1，</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28\">20:28；</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">羅馬書9:5；</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">希伯來書1:8；</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">彼得後書1:1</a>；可能還有<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">約翰福音1:18</a>）。然而，這個稱呼完全符合基督的角色和屬性以及祂所接受的崇拜。此處使用這個稱呼可能是為了表明基督並非是被提升到其他神明地位的普通人而已（見<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"25102\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleStudyNotes\">提多書1:12註釋</span>）。當這封信寫成時，基督徒越來越堅信唯有基督才應被稱為神（divine），而非統治者和皇帝。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "56002013",
          "start_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:13",
          "end_ref": "56002013",
          "end_ref_usfm": "TIT 2:13"
        }
      ],
      "resource": [
        {
          "reference_id": 16535,
          "content_id": 313639,
          "resource_code": "TyndaleStudyNotes",
          "label": "提摩太前書 6:14",
          "language": "zht"
        },
        {
          "reference_id": 25102,
          "content_id": 159043,
          "resource_code": "TyndaleStudyNotes",
          "label": "提多書 1:12",
          "language": "zht"
        }
      ]
    }
